ROSEBURG FOREST PRODUCTS COMPANY FERC ELECTRIC MBR TARIFF, VOLUME NO. 1
Availability
Roseburg Forest Products Company ("RFP") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale.
Applicability
This Tariff is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by RFP not otherwise subject to a particular Tariff of RFP.
Rates
All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and RFP.
Other Terms and Conditions
All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and RFP.
Compliance with Commission Regulations
Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority
The Commission has granted the following waivers to RFP:
1. Subparts B and C of Part 35, regarding the filing of Tariff, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.12(b), 35.15 and 35.16;
2. Part 41, regarding accounts, records, and memoranda;
3. Part 101, regarding the uniform system of accounts; and
4. Part 141, regarding statements and reports, with the exception of 18 CFR Section;Section;141.14, .15 (2001). RFP remains obligated to file Form No. 80 and the Annual Conveyance Report.
RFP Corp., Docket No. ER01-2830-0001, at 1-2 (Dec. 13, 2001) (unpublished letter order).
Seller Category
Seller is Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
Effective Date
The effective date of this tariff is as set forth by the Commission.
